The paper discusses the formalization of epistemic reasoning in multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of logic in reasoning also suggests that the paper could be categorized under Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The focus on multi-agent systems and planning suggests that the paper could also be categorized under Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Planning and Scheduling (cs.PL). Finally, the mention of different domains where reasoning about others' beliefs could lead to winning strategies or changing a group of agents' view of the world suggests that the paper could also be categorized under Systems and Control (cs.SY).
